ğŸŸ¢ Beginner Angular Topics â€” Interview Q&A with Code Snippets

âœ… 1. What is Angular?
Q1: What is Angular and how is it different from AngularJS?â€¨A:â€¨Angular is a TypeScript-based front-end web application framework developed by Google. It is used to build SPA (Single Page Applications).
Feature	Angular (v2+)	AngularJS
Language	TypeScript	JavaScript
Architecture	Component-based	MVC-based
Mobile Support	Yes	No
âœ… 2. Angular CLI
Q2: What is Angular CLI and what are its benefits?â€¨A: Angular CLI is a command-line tool to scaffold and manage Angular applications.
Key Benefits:
* Quick project setup
* Built-in tools (testing, linting, build)
* Code generation
Q3: How do you create a new Angular app using CLI?
npm install -g @angular/cli
ng new my-app
cd my-app
ng serve

âœ… 3. Angular Project Structure
Q4: What are the main folders and files in a new Angular project?â€¨A:
* src/app: Contains all app components, modules, services
* main.ts: Entry point
* index.html: Main HTML shell
* angular.json: Project config
* package.json: Dependencies

âœ… 4. Components
Q5: What is a component in Angular?â€¨A: A component controls a part of the UI. It has:
* HTML template
* TypeScript class
* CSS styles
Example:
// app.component.ts
@Component({
  selector: 'app-root',
  templateUrl: './app.component.html'
})
export class AppComponent {
  title = 'Hello Angular!';
}
Q6: How do you create a component using CLI?
ng generate component my-component

âœ… 5. Templates
Q7: What are Angular templates?â€¨A: Templates define the HTML view. They can include:
* Interpolation: {{ value }}
* Binding: [value]="val" or (click)="method()"
Example:
<h1>{{ title }}</h1>
<button (click)="sayHello()">Click</button>
sayHello() {
  alert("Hello!");
}

âœ… 6. Data Binding
Q8: What are the types of data binding in Angular?
Type	Syntax	Description
Interpolation	{{ expression }}	Display data
Property Binding	[property]="exp"	Bind property to value
Event Binding	(event)="handler"	Respond to events
Two-Way Binding	[(ngModel)]="val"	Sync between view and model
Example:
<input [(ngModel)]="name" />
<p>Hello, {{ name }}</p>

âœ… 7. Directives
Q9: What is the difference between structural and attribute directives?
Directive Type	Example	Description
Structural	*ngIf, *ngFor	Adds/removes DOM elements
Attribute	[ngClass], [ngStyle]	Modifies appearance or behavior
Example:
<div *ngIf="isVisible">Visible!</div>
<ul>
  <li *ngFor="let item of items">{{ item }}</li>
</ul>

âœ… 8. Pipes
Q10: What are Angular pipes?â€¨A: Pipes transform data in the template.
Built-in examples:
<p>{{ birthday | date:'longDate' }}</p>
<p>{{ price | currency:'INR' }}</p>
Custom Pipe Example:
@Pipe({name: 'capitalize'})
export class CapitalizePipe implements PipeTransform {
  transform(value: string): string {
    return value.charAt(0).toUpperCase() + value.slice(1);
  }
}

âœ… 9. Services and Dependency Injection
Q11: What is a service in Angular?â€¨A: A service is a class that provides business logic or data.
Q12: What is Dependency Injection (DI)?â€¨A: DI is a design pattern used to inject services into components.
Example:
@Injectable({ providedIn: 'root' })
export class LoggerService {
  log(msg: string) {
    console.log(msg);
  }
}

// In component
constructor(private logger: LoggerService) {}

âœ… 10. Modules
Q13: What is the role of NgModule in Angular?â€¨A: It declares components, directives, and pipes; and imports other modules.
Example:
@NgModule({
  declarations: [AppComponent],
  imports: [BrowserModule, FormsModule],
  bootstrap: [AppComponent]
})
export class AppModule {}

