@NgModule({
  imports: [FormsModule]
})
export class AppModule {}

ğŸ§  Follow-Up:
"What happens if you use [(ngModel)] with Reactive Forms?"
âŒ ngModel should not be used with FormControl or reactive forms â€” it causes expressionChangedAfterItHasBeenChecked error. Use ReactiveFormsModule and formControlName instead.

âœ… 2. Topic: Difference Between Interpolation & Property Binding
ğŸ’¬ Interviewer Asks:
"Whatâ€™s the difference between {{ title }} and [value]="title"?"

âœ… Answer:
Syntax	Use Case
{{ title }}	Interpolation â€” for text inside HTML
[value]	Property Binding â€” for binding DOM properties
ğŸ”§ Code Example:
<!-- Interpolation -->
<h1>{{ title }}</h1>

<!-- Property Binding -->
<input [value]="title" />
title = 'Angular Demo';
âœ… {{ }} doesn't work for properties like disabled, href, src, etc.

âœ… 3. Topic: Difference Between ngIf and Hidden
ğŸ’¬ Interviewer Asks:
"Whatâ€™s the difference between using *ngIf="false" and hidden="true" on an element?"

âœ… Answer:
Feature	*ngIf	hidden
Behavior	Removes element from DOM	Hides it via CSS
Performance	Better (frees memory)	Just visual toggle
Use Case	Conditional rendering	Quick visibility control
ğŸ”§ Example:
<!-- Completely removes element -->
<p *ngIf="false">This is removed</p>

<!-- Stays in DOM but hidden -->
<p [hidden]="true">This is hidden</p>

âœ… 4. Topic: Content Projection (ng-content)
ğŸ’¬ Interviewer Asks:
"How would you pass custom content inside a reusable card component?"

âœ… Answer:
Use <ng-content> for content projection (slot-like behavior).

ğŸ”§ Code Snippet:
