  this.fetchUsers();
}
âœ… Avoid fetching data in the constructor â€” constructor is for setting up DI, not logic.

ğŸ§  Follow-Up:
"What if I want to act only when a specific @Input() changes?"
âœ… Use ngOnChanges():
ngOnChanges(changes: SimpleChanges): void {
  if (changes['inputValue']) {
    // Do something when inputValue changes
  }
}

âœ… 6. Topic: Difference Between Declarations and Imports
ğŸ’¬ Interviewer Asks:
â€œI declared a component in the wrong place, and Angular gave an error. Whatâ€™s the difference between declarations, imports, and exports?â€

âœ… Answer:
Term	Used For
declarations	Components, Pipes, Directives of this module
imports	Other modules whose exports you need
exports	Making declarations available to others
ğŸ§  Use Case:
* If HeaderComponent is used only in this module â†’ declare it
* If you want to use HeaderComponent in other modules â†’ export it

âœ… 7. Topic: String Interpolation Inside Attributes
ğŸ’¬ Interviewer Asks:
â€œCan you use {{ }} inside attribute values like <input value="{{title}}">?â€

âœ… Answer:
Yes, but it's discouraged for non-text properties. Use property binding ([value]) instead.

ğŸ”§ Example:
<!-- Allowed but not best practice -->
